snAgentPoeGblPowerCapacityTotal.name: snAgentPoeGblPowerCapacityTotal
snAgentPoeGblPowerCapacityTotal.description: This object shows the total inline power capacity available in the device, measured in mWatts.

snAgentPoeGblPowerCapacityFree.name: snAgentPoeGblPowerCapacityFree
snAgentPoeGblPowerCapacityFree.description: This object shows the inline power capacity currently available in the device which is unallocated, measured in mWatts.

snAgentPoeGblPowerAllocationsRequestsHon.name: snAgentPoeGblPowerAllocationsRequestsHonored
snAgentPoeGblPowerAllocationsRequestsHon.description: This object shows number of times the inline power allocations requests honored.

snAgentPoePortTable.name: snAgentPoePortTable
snAgentPoePortTable.description: A table of POE port information.

snAgentPoePortEntry.name: snAgentPoePortEntry
snAgentPoePortEntry.description: A row in the POE port table.

snAgentPoePortNumber.name: snAgentPoePortNumber
snAgentPoePortNumber.description: The port number in ifIndex value.

snAgentPoePortControl.name: snAgentPoePortControl
snAgentPoePortControl.description: Control inline power on/off to a port. If a port does not have inline power capability, reading this object returns 'other(1)'.

snAgentPoePortWattage.name: snAgentPoePortWattage
snAgentPoePortWattage.description: Adjust the inline power wattage. Valid value between 1000 to 15400(IEEE802_3AF)/30000(IEEE802_3AT). Each unit is milliwatts. This object can only be set after snSwIfInLinePowerControl has been set to 'enable(3)' or 'enableLegacyDevice(4)'. If a port does not have inline power capability, reading this object returns undefined value.

snAgentPoePortClass.name: snAgentPoePortClass
snAgentPoePortClass.description: Adjust the inline power class. Valid value between 0 to 3(IEEE802_3AF)/4(IEEE802_3AT). This object can only be set after snSwIfInLinePowerControl has been set to 'enable(3)' or 'enableLegacyDevice(4)'. If a port does not have inline power capability, reading this object returns undefined value.

snAgentPoePortPriority.name: snAgentPoePortPriority
snAgentPoePortPriority.description: Inline power allocation priority for the power device 0- Not a POE port, 1- Critical, 2- High, 3- Low, 4- Medium, 5- other.

snAgentPoePortConsumed.name: snAgentPoePortConsumed
snAgentPoePortConsumed.description: Inline power consumed by the port. Each unit is milliwatts.

snAgentPoePortType.name: snAgentPoePortType
snAgentPoePortType.description: Inline Power device type 802.3af, 802.3at or Legacy device.

snAgentPoeModuleTable.name: snAgentPoeModuleTable
snAgentPoeModuleTable.description: A table of POE Module configuration.

snAgentPoeModuleEntry.name: snAgentPoeModuleEntry
snAgentPoeModuleEntry.description: A row in the POE Module table.

snAgentPoeModuleNumber.name: snAgentPoeModuleNumber
snAgentPoeModuleNumber.description: This objects talks about POE module number.

snAgentPoeModuleBudget.name: snAgentPoeModuleBudget
snAgentPoeModuleBudget.description: This objects talks about module power budget in watts.

snAgentPoeModuleMaxPDTypeSupport.name: snAgentPoeModuleMaxPDTypeSupport
snAgentPoeModuleMaxPDTypeSupport.description: This object talks about the POE module type which is capable to support Power Device (PD) type ieee802.3af or ieee802.3at(also called POE plus)type. Module which support ieee802.3at can also support ieee802.3af but reverse is not true.

snAgentPoeUnitTable.name: snAgentPoeUnitTable
snAgentPoeUnitTable.description: A table of POE informaion for each unit. Only the unit that has POE capability appears in a table row

snAgentPoeUnitEntry.name: snAgentPoeUnitEntry
snAgentPoeUnitEntry.description: A row in the POE Unit table.

snAgentPoeUnitIndex.name: snAgentPoeUnitIndex
snAgentPoeUnitIndex.description: The Index to POE unit Table.

snAgentPoeUnitPowerCapacityTotal.name: snAgentPoeUnitPowerCapacityTotal
snAgentPoeUnitPowerCapacityTotal.description: This object shows the total inline power capacity available on that unit (device), measured in mWatts.

snAgentPoeUnitPowerCapacityFree.name: snAgentPoeUnitPowerCapacityFree
snAgentPoeUnitPowerCapacityFree.description: This object shows the inline power capacity currently available on that unit (device) which is unallocated, measured in mWatts.

snAgentPoeUnitPowerAllocationsRequestsHo.name: snAgentPoeUnitPowerAllocationsRequestsHonored
snAgentPoeUnitPowerAllocationsRequestsHo.description: This object shows number of times the inline power allocations requests honored on that unit (device).
